Murang'a Seal boosted their Kenyan Premier League promotion hopes after thumping Mombasa Elite 3-0 at Mbaraki Stadium on Thursday. Dennis Wabwire was the toast of the day, his hat-trick separating the two sides at full-time. The outcome fired Seal to second on the log with 61 points, keeping the promotion battle open as they joined Muhoroni Youth and Fortune Sacco in the frantic search for the remaining two slots. On Wednesday, APS Bomet gained direct promotion to the country's top-flight competition after sealing the top spot following their hard-fought 1-0 win over Mara Sugar at the IAAF Stadium in Bomet. The win propelled the law enforcers to 68 points. Seal host Shabana at the St. SÃ©bastien stadium in their penultimate encounter before their crunch final fixture against APS Bomet. Elsewhere, Shabana edged Kisumu All Stars 2-1 to reignite their dreams of returning to top-flight action. The Kisii-based side netted through Brian Michiru and Vincent Nyabuto while Kisumu All Stars grabbed a consolation through Rolex Ouma. Former KPL side Vihiga United beat Kibera Black Stars 2-1 at the Mumias Sports complex 